
Step 1 – Create a Test Topic in DC
Run inside a DC broker pod:

oc rsh -n prod-dc-kafka prod-dc-kafka-cluster-broker-0
cd /opt/kafka/bin/

./kafka-topics.sh \
--bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
--create \
--topic test-smm-sync \
--partitions 1 \
--replication-factor 3

./kafka-topics.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --list
exit


You should see test-smm-sync in the list.



Step 2 – Produce a Message into That Topic

Run inside the same DC broker pod:

oc rsh -n prod-dc-kafka prod-dc-kafka-cluster-broker-0
cd /opt/kafka/bin/

./kafka-console-producer.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic test-smm-sync


Now type a few messages manually (press Enter after each):
saadi
omkar
suraj
nikhil




Step 3 – Check if Topic Appears in DR

Run inside a DR broker pod:

oc rsh -n prod-dr-kafka prod-dr-kafka-cluster-broker-0
cd /opt/kafka/bin/

./kafka-topics.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --list | grep test-smm-sync


Step 4 – Consume Messages in DR

Still inside DR broker pod:

./kafka-console-consumer.sh \
--bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
--topic test-smm-sync \
--from-beginning \
--timeout-ms 5000
